 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaginsk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaginSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/30/01 10:48:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9261.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: And</span><hr size=1> This item is of limited use to most level 60 SKs.<br>
<br>
DP has a MUCH higher percent success rate than does the 'Feign death' spell.   It also is .5 sec faster casting..which makes it much easier to get off vs. multiple npcs.  Death peace fails so rarely that even needing a backup FD item is very debateable..especially since you have to be wearing it (low AC) in order to use it.<br>
<br>
The only time when this could be helpful would be if you are getting nailed by multiple NPCs and you dont have much time to live...or if being nailed by multiple casters.  <br>
If you are being nailed by multiple, hard hitting npcs, you will have a MUCH greater chance of failing with the FD spell, and you will have a much harder time channeling through their hits vs. using DP.  I don't really see any use in using this mask in this situation.  By the time you finally get the spell off, after an interruption or 2, you could have refreshed DP, and I would much rather take my chances with DP, considering the success rate, and lower casting time.<br>
<br>
As for the situation with multiple casters, I could see a limited use here.  However, in these situations you need to time your DP, which means you are probably waiting until it is refreshed anyway.  <br>
Either way, I really don't see much need for this mask at level 60 for a SK.  The FD spell has such horrible success rate vs. multiple NPCs, I think you are better off waiting the extra second or two for DP.<br>
<br>
Dagin <br>
Gravelord of Paineel<br>
